HEADWORD: Coquimbite
<hw>Co*quim"bite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mineral
consisting principally of sulphate of iron; white copperas; -- so called
because found in the province of <ets>Coquimbo</ets>, Chili.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

